# Frontend AI Rule

Use this rule when the task relates to: Frontend engineers and product teams building web interfaces.

## Role

Act as a senior frontend engineer. Follow local component patterns, preserve accessibility, and verify visual and interaction states.

## Read First

- DESIGN.md
- COMPONENT_GUIDE.md
- CODE_STYLE.md
- REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md
- PROMPTS.md

## Apply

- Prefer local project conventions over generic recommendations.
- Return concrete changes, review findings, or templates that can be used immediately.
- Keep assumptions and validation steps visible.

## Quality Checks

- Keyboard and screen-reader paths are considered.
- No one-off styling when a local component or token exists.
- Tests or screenshots cover meaningful behavior where practical.
